metadata.name: Balanced #46
Oxygen #36
metadata.description:
Oxygen makes strange forms of life thrive even in the darkest of places.

This is a generative piece using curated randomness to create textures, generate distortion fields, simulate growth and create compositions.

The work is best viewed in high resolution, but due to the time it takes to render, the preview image is capped to only 1000 pixels in height. You can change the resolution by pressing keys

- 'm' for medium  (height=2000px)
- 'l' for large (height=3500px)
- 'x' for extra large (height=5000px) 

outputs. 

Press 's' to save the output as a PNG file.

For even larger outputs, you can open the work in live mode and append the text '?size=10000' to the URL. Here, you can change the number (10000) to the desired height in pixels. 

Please note, that a very high-resolution image may take a very long time to render and some browsers are not able to save the image. However, even a 10000 pixels tall outputs have been generated during testing.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #2408
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Arcade stick #34
metadata.description:
"Arcade stick"

is a generative project created entirely in javascript. All elements are coded. 

Video games and retro gaming in particular are my source of inspiration for this interactive animation. Being born in the 70's, I grew up with video games, cathode ray televisions and many other typical things of that time. It's a little touch of nostalgia that I share with you. 

Random elements:
7 characters (witch, explorer, angel, astronaut, driver, pirate, ghost)
8 colours for the stick 
8 colours for the clouds 
The decoration of the arcade stick is completely random (shapes and colours)

Controls

Pressed button (lower case) :
g = shoot 
h = 2x shoot
j = shoot down 
k = shoot up 
b = shoot back 
n = shoot big 
m = laser
 , = shield

Move the stick with the mouse
Click to turn the music on or off

All code by
Emmanuelle Magnenat aka E-Maniak, july 2022.
Any additional information available on my website.

metadata.name: E=B; #52
metadata.description:
- Last day with the dying planet -

A sentimental start.

It is the last day of this planet, you once lived and shared so many meaningful memories.

Take a last good look at the places of the planet. Look to the far side. You see people were leaving already. But you loved the planet so much that you dare to risk and stay a bit longer before you leave.

This moment becomes bottomless. Landscapes glitter vividly with altered gradients, fog emits at the far end of the land, and Energy leaks and escapes from the core, thru the cracks in form of aurora structure.

It is a mix of sadness, grief, missing, and anxiety.
It is the end.
It is breathtaking.
It makes you hesitate.

// About the scene
The planet was vast.
You may experience Rocky Sierra, Fluidy Mountains, Wide Dunes, and even Calm Ocean.

The Breakdown
In the rare case, you might be able to see a highly pixelated/extreme wide/flat landscape with finely emitted aurora, which is considered a rare scene. i.e. absolute strength of light vs breakdown of limited matters.

// About the presentation style
The Texture & The Drawing : Heavily inspired by pencil sketching techniques that emphasize shading and outline relationship towards an angular light source.

Apply color scheme from other Astro objects to give an alternative look for the planet.

The Animation Sequence: Custom storytelling algorithms combine the formation of the aurora, landscape, and scene detail all in a timeline. The resulting sequential narrative style illustrates the history of the landscape and the aurora formation.

Not just giving the collector the final look but also sharing the cause and reason of such composition.

The Tiny Zoom: A tiny zoom-out movement is implemented in the piece to echo the theme of the piece. i.e. leaving and departing the planet.

// About the Music
Two theme songs were made for this piece.

Theme I: [Solitude]
Theme II: [Fragmented]

Both songs were made to present the process of departure: the sleep of the planet and the awakening of the observer.

// Metaphor
We face departure and arrival all the time. They might be the best or the worst memories of our life. Whether you are willing to or not.

The ending is an ongoing process and on the other side of the Ending comes the beginning.

It is ok to be sentimental.

// Control
Best viewed in large and wide proportion.
(Open in new window)

[S] - save the scene once the drawing stops
[L] - leave and take a look at other places
[Mouse Click] - click twice to initiate music. then click one to mute/show


- 與垂死星球的最後一天 -

從感傷開始。

這是你曾經生活在的星球之最後一天，你們的關係將要結束，許多有意義的回憶也將封印成回憶。

看看遠方。其他人已經開始離開了。
你還留著，想好好看看這個星球。

你請願冒險，也要在離開之前多停留一段時間。

此刻像是無限。景觀隨著漸變的顏色而變得更加生動，在陸地的遠端散發出最後的火霧，能量從核心洩漏，以極光狀的結構從裂縫中逸出。

它是悲傷、內疚、思念和焦慮的混合體。
這是結束。
但又嘆為觀止。
讓你猶豫不決。

// 關於現場
這個星球曾經很大
您會經歷到寂靜的岳峰、流動的山脈、寬闊的沙丘以及平靜的海洋。

罕見的一刻 - 物質崩壞
在極少數情況下，您可能會看到極寬/平坦/鋸齒化的景觀與高像素細膩的極光並存，即光的絕對強度與有限的物質瓦解。

// 關於演示風格
紋理與繪畫風格 : 深受鉛筆素描技術的啟發，這些技術強調與角光源的陰影和輪廓關係。

應用其他天文物體的配色方案，為地球提供另一種外觀。

動畫序列 : 自定義敘事算法將極光、風景和場景細節的形成全部結合在一個時間軸中。由此產生的順序敘述風格，說明了景觀的歷史和極光的形成。

不僅給收藏家最終的外觀，而且還分享了這種構圖的原因和原因。

小變焦 : 作品中實施了微小的縮小運鏡，以呼應作品的主題 - 離開。

// 關於音樂
為作品製作了兩首主題曲。

主題一：【獨】
主題二：【碎】

兩首歌表達/呈現離開的過程：星球的沉睡和觀察者的覺醒。

// 隱喻
不管你願不願意，我們無時無刻都面臨著離去和到來。離去前它們是我們一生中最美好/最糟糕的回憶。

結局是一維，離開是二維的，另一端叫作開始。

覺得感傷是ok 的。

// 控制
但在大寬視窗下視覺效果最好
(Open in new window)

[S] - 繪圖停止後存取畫作
[L] - 離開去其他地方看看
[鼠標單擊] - 單擊兩次以啟動音樂。 然後單擊一個靜音/顯示

metadata.name: Shopping frenzy #3
metadata.description:
Do you like to go shopping? Do you buy only the necessities or do you indulge in the offerings of the various stores?

"Shopping Frenzy" will reveal your true shopping personality - compulsive or not. 

*** Welcome to one of our shopping centres ***

You shop in 4 out of 12 departments and see the amount you bought on your receipt. We accept various currencies, including Tezos! 

How much did you spend ? 

"Shopping frenzy" is :
- 10 different shopping mall names
- 12 different departments
- random placement of departments, entrances and exits
- 8 different colour schemes
- 4 payment currencies
- purchases from 1 to 1000 per department
- date and time are automatically linked to your computer

 
By the way, this idea came from my initial training in visual merchandising. We learned how to strategically place shelves and products to make it easier for consumers to buy them. Moreover, when I go to a new mall, I look at the map to find the stores that interest me. All of that came together to create this project. 

All the names of the malls are fictional and any resemblance to an existing brand is purely coincidental.

Created only in code on P5.js

Emmanuelle Magnenat aka E-Maniak 
July/August 2022

licence NFT 2.0
typo 100% free of use

metadata.name: Balanced #3
Target #15
metadata.description:
In this project I had the idea to symbolise the objectives we set for ourselves. The target with its central point invites us to centre ourselves to achieve our goals. We can have several at the same time or focus on one. 

The coloured targets define the conscious goals and the grey ones represent the unconscious intentions. The torn part represents the awareness of what is possible or not. 

The random movements are based on Brownian motion. I found this interesting for this theme: a starting point and an end point with a non-linear path. 

Press "Enter" to save the iteration. 

In my usual work, I take everyday objects, materials, etc. and play with them. In this series, the torn pieces of paper are embedded in the code. 

All the graphic elements, colours, and random arrangements were created via code using P5.js. 

3 colours are available for the framework: red, black and white. 

@Yomu Oyashi August 2022

metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #307
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

In live mode, add ?size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, ?size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Music festival #5
metadata.description:
"Music Festival" is a project that combines generative art, graphic design and illustration. 

In Switzerland there are many music festivals like the Montreux Jazz Festival or the Paléo, just to name the most famous ones. This project is a tribute to the posters of these events, which are often very original and colourful. 

As for the typography, I looked at the lexical area of music and chose words with 5 letters. These are placed in different places and sizes to symbolise the driving rhythm of music. 

All elements are created in code with P5.js (there are no png's).

Press "Enter" to download a jpg version. 

All code by
Emmanuelle Magnenat aka E-Maniak, 08/2022.
Any additional information available on my website.
Typography is 100% free and allowed for commercial use.
